<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.2.1">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://linuxtus.com/feed/programming.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://linuxtus.com/" rel="alternate" type="text/html"/><updated>2022-08-02T20:56:21+07:00</updated><id>https://linuxtus.com/feed/programming.xml</id><title type="html">LinuxTus | Programming</title><subtitle>Where to share IT Blog</subtitle><author><name>tgbao2703</name></author><entry xml:lang="en"><title type="html">How To Speed Up Python Programs With These Tips</title><link href="https://linuxtus.com/python-tricks-code-faster/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How To Speed Up Python Programs With These Tips"/><published>2021-11-18T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2021-12-16T14:59:47+07:00</updated><id>https://linuxtus.com/python-tricks-code-faster</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://linuxtus.com/python-tricks-code-faster/">&lt;p&gt;Not same as Java, C++, C# which are compiled languages, Python is Interpreted. You write a Python program and then tell the interpreter to execute it. It runs the program one line at a time, translating each line before running it. Therefore, your Python program will be executed very slowly. However, we can speed up Python excretion by optimizing our code mentioned in this article. Some tips you will already know, but some ones can be your new knowledge today. Following this guide, you can speed up your programs and also code faster.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id=&quot;toc-post&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/tips-code-python-faster-speed-up-800-72a7366fd.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Tips to speed up Python Programs and code faster&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/tips-code-python-faster-speed-up-1000-b6e052536.webp 1000w, /generated/assets/img/posts/20/tips-code-python-faster-speed-up-1280-b6e052536.webp 1280w&quot; width=&quot;1280&quot; height=&quot;710&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;tips-to-code-python-faster&quot;&gt;Tips to Code Python Faster&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;1-install-the-latest-python&quot;&gt;1. Install the latest Python&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;It is always the best way to speed up your python program by &lt;a href=&quot;https://linuxtus.com/install-python-ubuntu/&quot;&gt;installing the latest Python&lt;/a&gt;. Latest Python, which means that it contains improved performance modules, adds some new syntax to the language, a few minor tweaks to existing behavior, and most importantly, a slew of a bunch of speed improvements. Therefore, I think you should update your Python to the latest Python version before continuing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;2-using-builtin-functions&quot;&gt;2. Using Builtin Functions&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Builtin functions is a collection code that is coded by Python (and community). Using builtin functions is one of the best ways to speed up your python programs. The advantages of using these functions are:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Reducing code duplication&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Increasing the code’s clarity&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Reusability of code&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;The concealment of information&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Improve the speed of execution.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Replace your custom created function with a library function and compare the program’s performance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/python-built-in-functions-800-c8b36a8d8.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Python Built-in Functions Speed Up Python&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/python-built-in-functions-1000-9a5b11a56.webp 1000w, /generated/assets/img/posts/20/python-built-in-functions-1300-9a5b11a56.webp 1300w&quot; width=&quot;1300&quot; height=&quot;650&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;3-using-list-comprehension&quot;&gt;3. Using List Comprehension&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;List Comprehension is a powerful syntax in Python. It provides a new way to construct a list from an old one or in-line loop fast, in combination with given conditions. You should consider this example.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-python&quot; data-lang=&quot;python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;kn&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nn&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;normal_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;():&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# main &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;[]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;ow&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;range&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;):&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;res&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;append&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;normal: --- %s seconds ---&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;faster_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;():&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# main &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;ow&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;range&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;faster: --- %s seconds ---&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;res&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;normal_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;faster_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;After running this script, we can see that list comprehension is 50% faster than the normal way. This image is taken when I was &lt;a href=&quot;https://linuxtus.com/install-alacritty-terminal-emulator-ubuntu/&quot;&gt;Using Alacritty&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-list-comprehension-800-4f97d7e4a.png&quot; alt=&quot;Speed Up Python Programs With List Comprehension&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-list-comprehension-1000-a23bea96d.webp 1000w, /generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-list-comprehension-1400-a23bea96d.webp 1400w&quot; width=&quot;1600&quot; height=&quot;866&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;List Comprehension&lt;/strong&gt; is the fastest and most direct method of accomplishing the same task. It’s a lot faster than using the append approach in Python. As a result, you should always strive to use a list comprehension solution. Read more about &lt;a href=&quot;https://docs.python.org/3/tutorial/datastructures.html#list-comprehensions&quot;&gt;List Comprehension&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;4-do-not-use-global-variables&quot;&gt;4. Do not use Global Variables&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Python has &lt;strong&gt;global&lt;/strong&gt; keyword to declare global variables. But global variables take higher time during operation than a local variable. So, do not use global variables if it is not necessary to speed up program.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;5-concating-string-with-join-function&quot;&gt;5. Concating String with Join Function&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;join&lt;/strong&gt; function is a built-in Python function that has the same function as the &lt;strong&gt;+&lt;/strong&gt; operator. Use this tip, you can speed up your Python programs and code faster. Below is the example and difference in both ways.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-python&quot; data-lang=&quot;python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;kn&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nn&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;normal_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;():&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# main &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ret&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;ow&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;range&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;):&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ret&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;+=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;normal: %s seconds&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;def&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nf&quot;&gt;faster_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;():&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# main &lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;ret&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;join&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;str&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;*&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;i&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;ow&quot;&gt;in&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;range&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;10000000&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;print&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s&quot;&gt;&quot;faster: %s seconds&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;%&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;-&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;start_time&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;))&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;normal_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;faster_way&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;In this example, you can reduce the execution time by 0.5 seconds.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-join-function-800-b22d97bc5.png&quot; alt=&quot;Speed Up Python Programs With List Comprehension&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-join-function-1000-2be4c7b17.webp 1000w, /generated/assets/img/posts/20/code-python-faster-with-join-function-1400-2be4c7b17.webp 1400w&quot; width=&quot;1600&quot; height=&quot;866&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When compared to simple concatenation, the &lt;a href=&quot;https://python-reference.readthedocs.io/en/latest/docs/str/join.html&quot;&gt;join method&lt;/a&gt; is both faster and more accurate. As a result, the method is more accurate, faster, and saves time. I hope it can help you in improving your python performance.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;6-using-multiple-assignments&quot;&gt;6. Using Multiple Assignments&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Rather than completing a single assignment, you should complete several. Because it can help your programs execute faster. Let consider this example to know:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-python&quot; data-lang=&quot;python&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# Single assignment &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;a&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;b&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;c1&quot;&gt;# Multiple assignments &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;a&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;b&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;c&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;n&quot;&gt;d&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;4&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;mi&quot;&gt;5&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;7-optimize-your-algorithm&quot;&gt;7. Optimize your algorithm&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;The algorithm has a huge impact on the execution time of the program. It will instruct the program on how to operate. Approach an optimal algorithm, which will make your program execute faster and you will code shorter&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;8-reducing-the-for-loop&quot;&gt;8. Reducing the For Loop&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;Loop optimization is the process of increasing loop execution speed while lowering loop overheads. It’s crucial for increasing cache performance and making the most of parallel processing capabilities. Therefore, we should use it carefully to make you program run faster.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h3 id=&quot;9-use-linux-instead-of-windows&quot;&gt;9. Use Linux instead of Windows&lt;/h3&gt; &lt;p&gt;According &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.phoronix.com/scan.php?page=article&amp;amp;item=ryzen3-windows-linux&amp;amp;num=8&quot;&gt;Phoronix Research&lt;/a&gt;, Python 3 performance is still much faster on Linux than Windows because &lt;a href=&quot;https://linuxtus.com/upgrade-to-ubuntu-21-10/&quot;&gt;Linux&lt;/a&gt; is more lighter then windows and it consume lesser memory of your system. So I think you should consider using Linux for big Python projects.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;conclusion&quot;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;In this guide, I introduced &lt;strong&gt;Tips to Code Python Faster&lt;/strong&gt;. I hope it will assist you in speeding up your python programs. If you are needed, please leave a comment below.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>tgbao2703</name></author><category term="programming"/><category term="python"/><category term="programming"/><summary type="html">Not same as Java, C++, C# which are compiled languages, Python is Interpreted. You write a Python program and then tell the interpreter to execute it. It runs the program one line at a time, translating each line before running it. Therefore, your Python program will be executed very slowly. However, we can speed up Python excretion by optimizing our code mentioned in this article. Some tips you will already know, but some ones can be your new knowledge today. Following this guide, you can speed up your programs and also code faster.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://linuxtus.com/assets/img/posts/20/tips-code-python-faster-speed-up.jpg"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://linuxtus.com/assets/img/posts/20/tips-code-python-faster-speed-up.jpg" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry><entry xml:lang="en"><title type="html">How to Lazy Load Adsense - New Code</title><link href="https://linuxtus.com/lazy-load-google-adsense-new-code/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="How to Lazy Load Adsense - New Code"/><published>2021-11-16T00:00:00+07:00</published><updated>2021-12-16T14:59:47+07:00</updated><id>https://linuxtus.com/lazy-load-google-adsense-new-code</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://linuxtus.com/lazy-load-google-adsense-new-code/">&lt;p&gt;Speed is very important for a website. It’s so important that Google has made it an actual ranking factor. You should work on making your site as fast and accessible as possible. If your website is using Google Adsense, it can be the first thing you must consider, because Adsense makes your website load very slowly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In this post, I will help you to know steps to lazy load Adsense in your website to improve page speed, so that your website will load faster and it can rank higher.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;div id=&quot;toc-post&quot;&gt;&lt;/div&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;what-is-google-adsense&quot;&gt;What is Google Adsense?&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;According to &lt;a href=&quot;https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Google_AdSense&quot;&gt;Wikipedia&lt;/a&gt;, Google AdSense is a Google program that allows website publishers in the Google Network of content sites to serve text, image, video, or interactive media advertisements that are tailored to the content and audience of their sites. Google is in charge of administering, sorting, and maintaining these advertisements.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Google AdSense is a program that allows publishers to profit from their online content. AdSense works by finding ads that are relevant to your site’s content and visitors. Advertisers who want to promote their products create and pay for the ads. The amount you earn will vary because these advertisers pay different prices for different ads.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;how-does-lazy-load-adsense-works&quot;&gt;How does Lazy Load Adsense works?&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;To increase performance and save system resources, lazy loading is the technique of postponing the loading or initialization of resources or objects until they are really needed. For example, if a web page contains an image that requires the user to scroll down to see, you can show a placeholder and then lazy load the complete image once the user reaches the desired spot.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/pagespeed-100-lazy-load-google-adsense-800-f09f6ab42.png&quot; alt=&quot;PageSpeed 100 After Lazy Load Adsense&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/pagespeed-100-lazy-load-google-adsense-1000-5f16f9875.webp 1000w, /generated/assets/img/posts/19/pagespeed-100-lazy-load-google-adsense-1400-5f16f9875.webp 1400w&quot; width=&quot;1599&quot; height=&quot;770&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;lazy-load-adsense-on-native-website&quot;&gt;Lazy Load Adsense on Native Website&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;blockquote&gt; &lt;p&gt;If your website is making money that depends on Google Adsense, you shouldn’t follow these steps, because it can reduce your earning money rapidly, but your website will load very fast.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/blockquote&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;step-highlight&quot;&gt;Step 1:&lt;/span&gt; Remove your old Google Adsense code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;By default, Google Adsense provides this code to use their’s service&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;script &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;async&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;async&apos;&lt;/span&gt; data-ad-client&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;ca-pub-xxxxxxxxxxx&apos;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nv&quot;&gt;src&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js&apos;&lt;/span&gt;/&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;Here Google Adsense also delay code by adding &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;async=&apos;async&apos;&lt;/code&gt; but it is still not optimized, because the ads still load on same page, which making the page heavy and taking a long time to finish loading the page. To lazy load Adsense and improve your page’s speed, you should remove this code, and replace with these below lazy load code&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;step-highlight&quot;&gt;Step 2:&lt;/span&gt; Replace with new Google Adsense code&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;After removing the old code, you need to replace with these code to apply lazy loading for your page. You should put them above &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;/body&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt; .&lt;/p&gt; &lt;figure class=&quot;highlight&quot;&gt;&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-bash&quot; data-lang=&quot;bash&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;script&amp;gt; window.addEventListener&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;load&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; var is_adsense_load &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 0 window.addEventListener&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;scroll&apos;&lt;/span&gt;, &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;function&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;()&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;k&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;is_adsense_load &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;==&lt;/span&gt; 0&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt; is_adsense_load &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; 1&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; var ele &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; document.createElement&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;script&apos;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; ele.async &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; ele.src &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;https://pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js&apos;&lt;/span&gt; var sc &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; document.getElementsByTagName&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&apos;script&apos;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)[&lt;/span&gt;0] sc.parentNode.insertBefore&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;ele, sc&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;(&lt;/span&gt;adsbygoogle &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;=&lt;/span&gt; window.adsbygoogle &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;||&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;[])&lt;/span&gt;.push&lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;({&lt;/span&gt; google_ad_client: &lt;span class=&quot;s2&quot;&gt;&quot;ca-pub-xxxxxxxxx&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, enable_page_level_ads: &lt;span class=&quot;nb&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;})&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;p&quot;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;})&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;o&quot;&gt;})&lt;/span&gt; &amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; &lt;p&gt;Don’t forget to replace your Adsense’s ID with ID in &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;ca-pub-xxxxxxxxxxxx&lt;/code&gt;. This approach will load ads once the user scrolls your web page. So that it will improve your website perfomance by using lazy load.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;lazy-loading-adsense-ads-on-wordpress-site&quot;&gt;Lazy Loading Adsense ads on WordPress site&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;WordPress is the world’s most popular website platform. It’s free, and comes with thousands of pre-made website designs and extensions. It’s extremely adaptable, and integrates with almost third-party tools. As a result, you can use the plugin to easily lazy load adsense ads units.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You must first install and activate Advanced Ads Pro in order to lazy load AdSense ads. After that, go to &lt;code class=&quot;language-plaintext highlighter-rouge&quot;&gt;Advanced Ads &amp;gt; Settings &amp;gt; Pro&lt;/code&gt; to enable this module.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/advanced-ads-lazy-load-adsense-wordpress-650-9d8da8ea3.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Advanced Ads Pro Lazy Load Adsense WordPress&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/advanced-ads-lazy-load-adsense-wordpress-650-f598def74.webp 650w&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;71&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You can now specify when the AdSense ads should appear. Set the number of pixels before they appear on the user’s screen and turn on the feature for the placements where you want your ads to load lazy.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;img class=&quot;lazyload rounded&quot; data-src=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/lazy-load-adsense-settings-wordpress-650-e64592986.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Lazy Loading Adsense Settings on WordPress&quot; data-srcset=&quot;/generated/assets/img/posts/19/lazy-load-adsense-settings-wordpress-650-e31c83638.webp 650w&quot; width=&quot;650&quot; height=&quot;144&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2 id=&quot;conclusion&quot;&gt;Conclusion&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Speed is one of important factors of Google Ranking so that it is necessary for your to optimize speed website and keep earning from Google Adsense. In this guide, I introduced &lt;strong&gt;Lazy Loading Goolge Adsense&lt;/strong&gt;. I hope it will help you in improving your site. Don’t forget to comment below if you are in needed.&lt;/p&gt;</content><author><name>tgbao2703</name></author><category term="programming"/><category term="google-adsense"/><category term="programming"/><summary type="html">Speed is very important for a website. It’s so important that Google has made it an actual ranking factor. You should work on making your site as fast and accessible as possible. If your website is using Google Adsense, it can be the first thing you must consider, because Adsense makes your website load very slowly.</summary><media:thumbnail xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="https://linuxtus.com/assets/img/posts/19/pagespeed-100-lazy-load-google-adsense.png"/><media:content medium="image" url="https://linuxtus.com/assets/img/posts/19/pagespeed-100-lazy-load-google-adsense.png" xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/"/></entry></feed>